As a whole, achievement of SDG 14 has been meagre, with no single country having achieved the four targets aimed for by the SDG 14 indicators (Figs. 1 and 2

                        ). Only two countries worldwide (Belgium and Germany) have achieved three of the targets (as indicated in Table 2
                        ). Less than 30% (45 countries) have achieved at least one of the targets, resulting in the significant finding that more than two thirds of coastal states globally (107 out of the 152) have not achieved a single of the four SDG targets under assessment. (See supplementary material 2 for more details on achievement of each country per indicator).
